===============================================================================
 LLVM Patch: Add AVA Vendor Extension Feature to RISCVFeatures.td
===============================================================================

File: llvm/lib/Target/RISCV/RISCVFeatures.td

Add the following SubtargetFeature definition in the "Vendor extensions"
section, near other vendor extension features (e.g., FeatureVendorXTHead*):

--- a/llvm/lib/Target/RISCV/RISCVFeatures.td
+++ b/llvm/lib/Target/RISCV/RISCVFeatures.td
@@ -xxx,6 +xxx,12 @@
+//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
+// AVA (AI Vector Accelerator) Vendor Extension
+//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
+
+def FeatureVendorXava
+    : SubtargetFeature<"xava", "HasVendorXava", "true",
+                       "AVA custom vector instructions for DNN inference",
+                       [FeatureStdExtZve32x]>;

Notes:
  - The feature name "xava" follows the RISC-V vendor extension naming
    convention (lowercase 'x' prefix + vendor name).
  - It depends on FeatureStdExtV because all AVA instructions use the OP-V
    major opcode (0x57) and operate on vector registers.
  - This adds a boolean field HasVendorXava to RISCVSubtarget that gates
    instruction selection in RISCVInstrInfoXava.td.

===============================================================================
 LLVM Patch: Register Extension in RISCVISAInfo.cpp
===============================================================================

File: llvm/lib/TargetParser/RISCVISAInfo.cpp

In the vendor extension table (search for "Vendor Extensions"),
add the following entry:

--- a/llvm/lib/TargetParser/RISCVISAInfo.cpp
+++ b/llvm/lib/TargetParser/RISCVISAInfo.cpp
@@ -xxx,6 +xxx,7 @@
     // Vendor Extensions
+    {"xava", {1, 0}},

Notes:
  - Version 1.0 corresponds to the initial AVA instruction set.
  - This enables -march=rv32imv_xava1p0 to be parsed by clang.

